# Next.js Landing Page Standards

## Stack
- **Next.js** (App Router), **TypeScript**, **Tailwind CSS v4**, **shadcn/ui**
- Prefer App Router conventions: `app/` layout, `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, route segments.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode on. Type props and component APIs; avoid `any`.
- Prefer `interface` for public shapes; use `type` for unions/utility types.
- Colocate types next to components or in `types/` when shared.

## Tailwind v4
- Use Tailwind v4 syntax and config (e.g. `@import "tailwindcss"` where applicable).
- Prefer utility classes; use `@layer` only when extending. No arbitrary values for one-offs that belong in design tokens.

## shadcn
- Use shadcn components from `components/ui/` as primitives; compose in feature/section components.
- Don’t alter shadcn source; extend via props, wrappers, or Tailwind.
- You can add components to your project (`bunx --bun shadcn@latest add <component name>`)


## SEO
- **Metadata**: Export `metadata` (and optionally `generateMetadata`) from `app/layout.tsx` and page-level `layout.tsx`/`page.tsx` (title, description, openGraph, twitter).
- **Semantic HTML**: Use `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, heading hierarchy (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`).
- **Performance**: Use next/image for images with `width`/`height` or `fill`; lazy-load below-the-fold.
- **Structured data**: Add JSON-LD where relevant (e.g. Organization, WebPage) in layout or page.

## Structure & Clean Code
- **Routes**: One primary page under `app/`; sections as components in `components/sections/` or `components/` (e.g. Hero, Features, CTA).
- **Components**: Small, single-purpose; props for configuration; no business logic in presentational components.
- **Naming**: PascalCase components; camelCase functions/variables; kebab-case for files if project uses it, else PascalCase for components.
- **Imports**: Absolute aliases (e.g. `@/components`) for clarity; group: React/Next → external → internal → types.
- **No duplication**: Shared UI and copy in reusable components or constants.

## Example (metadata + semantic section)

```tsx
// app/page.tsx
import { Hero } from "@/components/sections/Hero";
import { Features } from "@/components/sections/Features";

export const metadata = {
  title: "OfferOps – DevOps Interview War Room",
  description: "30-day program to clear DevOps interviews.",
};

export default function HomePage() {
  return (
    <main>
      <Hero />
      <Features />
    </main>
  );
}
```
